OL,3,CSir Chris Hoy shares 'shock' cancer
OL,4,Cdiagnosis
OL,6,FEdinburgh-born, Sir Chris took up
OL,7,Fcycling at the age of 14 and won his
OL,8,Ffirst Olympic medal, a team sprint
OL,9,Fsilver, at Sydney in 2000.
OL,11,FHe followed that up by winning gold in
OL,12,Fthe 1 km track time trial at Athens in
OL,13,F2004. He added to his gold medal haul
OL,14,Fby winning three more at Beijing four
OL,15,Fyears later and two at London 2012.
OL,17,FSir Chris also won 11 world titles and
OL,18,Fwas knighted in the 2008 New Year
OL,19,FHonours List after his success at the
OL,20,FBeijing Olympics.
